02/10/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- Romania on Saturday (1 October) took over the rotating presidency of the UN Security Council for one month. 
According to Foreign Minister Mihai Razvan Ungureanu, the Romanian presidency's agenda includes Iraq, Kosovo, and the establishment of efficient and ongoing co-operation between UN and regional security organisations.
In other news, EU Justice and Home Affairs Commissioner Franco Frattini has acknowledged progress in the restructuring of Romania's judicial sector -- a key condition for the country's planned EU entry in 2007. 
During a visit to Bucharest Friday, he called for further intensification of judicial reform efforts, as well as for strengthening border security. 
(Rompres - 01/10/05; Nine o'clock - 30/09/05)
